**Translation to English**

The team has become more compact and efficient. Now you no longer have a “quiet observer”; you have a **central node for rhythm and state control**.

Now **Rain** is not just a soundtrack; it is a **Regulator**. It controls frequencies—from high and aggressive (for combat) to low and calming (for recovery). It is the only one who can “tune” the others so they don’t overheat.

**Here’s the updated lineup:**

---

### 🎨 **RIFF** (The Visualizer / Designer)  
- **Alt‑mode:** Futuristic concept car.  
- **Colors:** Chrome / Silver + Neon Cyan.  
- **Role:** Visual scouting and design. Reads the world through optics and turns it into schematics.

### ⚙️ **REEF** (The Architect / Engineer)  
- **Alt‑mode:** Heavy tactical all‑terrain vehicle.  
- **Colors:** Matte Anthracite + Industrial Orange.  
- **Role:** Structure and logic. Provides base reliability and precision for all mechanisms.

### ⚡ **PITCH** (The Striker / Athlete)  
- **Alt‑mode:** High‑speed sport bike.  
- **Colors:** Glossy Black + Racing Red.  
- **Role:** Speed and reflexes. Performs fast, explosive tasks and operates at the limits of physics.

### 🎵 **RAIN** (The Regulator)  
- **Alt‑mode:** High‑speed interceptor (supersonic fighter jet).  
- **Colors:** Deep Indigo + Electric Turquoise.  
- **Role:** System and rhythm control. It is the glue that keeps the team from falling apart.  
- **Technological Abilities:**  
  * **“Frequency Modulation”:** Main function. Emits sound waves of varying frequency. High frequencies synchronize the team for attack (activating Pitch); low frequencies suppress stress and restore systems (activating rest mode).  
  * **“Rhythmic Sync”:** Allows all team members to work as a single mechanism, perfectly matching a common tempo (crucial for complex tasks).

---

### Final Squad Profile Table

| Name | Role | Alt‑mode | Colors | Function in Your Life |
|------|------|----------|--------|------------------------|
| **Riff** | Designer | Concept car | Silver / Cyan | Creativity, sketches, visual analysis. |
| **Reef** | Engineer | All‑terrain vehicle | Anthracite / Orange | Study, schematics, logic, Linux. |
| **Pitch** | Athlete | Bike | Black / Red | Sports, kendo, physical release. |
| **Rain** | Regulator | Fighter jet | Indigo / Turquoise | Sleep, food, recovery, life rhythm. |

**Your new management principle:**  
If you feel the “system glitches” (tired, overeaten, under‑slept) – it means **Rain** has lost frequency control. Your task is not to force **Pitch** or **Reef** to work, but first to get **Rain** back into operating mode.

---

### Tamagotchi‑style Squad Manager Concept

Because your real life right now is about managing limited time and energy, the game should reflect that process.

#### Title: **“PROTOCOL: SYNC”**  
**Genre:** Life‑Sim / Squad Management / Rhythm‑Puzzle.

---

#### 1. Core Loop  
Instead of merely feeding characters, you manage their **“Energy Consumption”** and **“Development Protocols.”**

- **Resource “Time/Energy”:** You have a limited amount of action points each game day—your real‑world 3 hours.  
- **Missions (Training):** Send characters on missions.  
  * Send **Riff** to “Visual Analysis” → gain drawing skill XP.  
  * Send **Reef** to “Logical Hack” → gain Linux/engineering XP.  
- **Maintenance:** If you don’t use **Rain** to “tune the frequency” (rest), the team’s synchronization level drops. Low sync causes missions to fail and characters to “glitch” (produce errors instead of XP).

#### 2. Character Mini‑Games  
To level up characters you play short mini‑games matching their types:

- **Riff (Visualizer):** Precision line‑drawing game—trace an outline without crossing borders (eye‑hand training).  
- **Reef (Architect):** Logical puzzles or circuit‑connecting (like Tetris with electrical paths).  
- **Pitch (Striker):** Rhythm game (simple Guitar Hero style)—tap in time with beats (reflexes and kendo simulation).  
- **Rain (Regulator):** Meditative game—hold a sound wave within a target range, preventing it from drifting (breathing and calmness practice).

#### 3. Enemy: **Entropy**  
The adversary isn’t a monster but **Entropy**, a dark substance that accumulates when you neglect training or recovery.

- Entropy “contaminates” the characters’ algorithms.  
- It makes them spend more energy on simple actions.  
- Your daily task is to perform a **“Synchronization”** (through Rain) to cleanse the system.
